This directory contains the main Android application source code.

Subdirectory license summary:
  - java/com/Regalia/: Mixed AGPL v3 and GPL v3
      See java/com/Regalia/README.license for per-file classification.
  - cpp/: Mixed AGPL v3 and GPL v3
      See cpp/README.license for per-file classification.
  - assets/: Combined work (AGPL v3 + GPL v3)
      See assets/README.license for details.
  - res/: AGPL v3 (original code and AI-generated assets)
      See res/README.license for details.
  - AndroidManifest.xml: AGPL v3 (original configuration)
      Permissions: INTERNET + ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE (Lichess Tablebase API),
      WAKE_LOCK (keep screen on during play), VIBRATE (haptic feedback),
      FOREGROUND_SERVICE + FOREGROUND_SERVICE_SPECIAL_USE (engine stability
      on Android 14/15 / Xiaomi HyperOS 3), POST_NOTIFICATIONS (Android 13+
      foreground-service notification). WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE /
      READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE are scoped to legacy Android versions only;
      READ_MEDIA_IMAGES was removed in v1.0.2 (the built-in file browser
      queries MediaStore.Files, not MediaStore.Images).
      v1.0.3: versionCode 102 → 103, versionName "1.0.2" → "1.0.3".
      v1.0.4: versionCode 103 → 104, versionName "1.0.3" → "1.0.4".

Overall, the application is a combined work under dual AGPL v3 + GPL v3
licensing. Only files containing DroidFish-derived code use GPL v3;
all other original code uses AGPL v3. Since AGPL v3 imposes stricter
requirements (including network interaction provisions), its obligations
effectively extend to the entire combined work.

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.

v1.0.4 EXPANSION (this round):
  - assets/chess.src/worker-pool.js (NEW FILE): Web Worker pool. The worker
      source is inlined as a string and instantiated via Blob URL (works
      with the WebView CSP `script-src 'unsafe-inline'`). The worker ships
      with a slim copy of chess primitives (attacked, getCtrlMap,
      makeMvInPlace, fenToState, stateToFEN, parsePGN, computeHeatmapStats)
      and handles 3 task types: 'parsePGN', 'computeHeatmapStats',
      'getCtrlMap'. Public Promise-based APIs: workerParsePGN(),
      workerComputeHeatmapStats(), workerGetCtrlMap(). Falls back to inline
      synchronous execution when Workers are unavailable.
  - assets/chess.src/pgn-standard.js (EXPANDED): added formatEmtTag() for
      [%emt HH:MM:SS] (spec §10.2.7, used for untimed games); NAG_MAP,
      nagToSymbol(), symbolToNag(), formatNagToken() for $1-$19 NAGs;
      formatCslTag()/formatCalTag()/parseCslTag()/parseCalTag() for
      Lichess/Chessbase [%csl ...] and [%cal ...] visual annotations;
      parseTimeControl()/formatTimeControl() supporting all 6 TimeControl
      formats (sudden/fischer/bronstein/usdelay/staged/hourglass).
  - assets/chess.src/ui.js (EXPANDED): New Game dialog gains a "Time
      Control" section (5-mode dropdown + base-time/increment/delay inputs).
      New state vars: dlgTimeControl, gameClocks, gameClockTimerId,
      gameClockExpired. New functions: initGameClocks(), _tickGameClock(),
      _onGameClockExpired(), recordMoveEnd(), formatClock(),
      _updateClockDisplay(). executeMove() now calls recordMoveEnd() and
      _computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations() per move.
  - assets/chess.src/ai-bridge.js (EXPANDED): _buildPGNString() now emits
      [TimeControl "..."] header when game is timed; per-move comments now
      include [%emt] (untimed) or [%clk] (timed), plus [%csl] and [%cal]
      from the visual annotations cache.
  - assets/stats.html (EXPANDED): New "Visual Annotations" stats section
      tallies [%csl] G/B/R/Y counts and NAG $1-$6 distribution from the
      PGN text. New i18n strings: time_control_mode, visual_annotations,
      nag_*, blue_arrows, red_arrows, green_squares, yellow_arrows.
  - assets/chess.src/game-logic.js (EXPANDED): New i18n strings:
      time_control_label, time_control_off, time_control_sudden,
      time_control_fischer, time_control_bronstein, time_control_usdelay,
      time_control_base_min, time_control_inc_sec, time_control_delay_sec,
      time_control_note, time_control_white_clock, time_control_black_clock,
      time_control_flag_fell, time_control_low.

v1.0.4 changes:
  - AndroidManifest.xml: versionCode/versionName bumped to 104 / "1.0.4".
  - res/values/strings.xml: app_name string updated to "Regalia v1.0.4".
  - assets/chess.src/chess960.js (NEW FILE): Chess960 implementation —
      SP-ID generator (0..959), Shredder-FEN castling rights encoder/
      decoder (HAah format), 960 castling legality checker (King ends on
      g1/c1, Rook ends on f1/d1 — same final squares as standard chess),
      initChess960State() to build a complete game state from SP-ID,
      setChess960Mode()/isChess960Mode() bridge helpers.
  - assets/chess.src/pgn-standard.js (NEW FILE): Standardized PGN encoder/
      decoder following the 1994 PGN spec. sevenTagRoster() always emits
      the mandatory 7 tags. composePGN() builds movetext with ~78-column
      wrapping + Result terminator. parseStandardPGN() tolerant parser
      auto-corrects nested {} comments, unclosed comments, 0-0 → O-O,
      invalid SAN tokens, missing Result, missing [SetUp "1"].
  - assets/chess.src/ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNString() rewritten to use
      composePGN() — emits Seven-Tag Roster + supplementary tags
      ([Variant "Chess960"], [SetUp "1"], [FEN "..."], [PlyCount "..."]) +
      [%eval] annotations inside comments. Chess960 FEN uses Shredder
      castling format via toShredderCastling().
  - assets/chess.src/tablebase.js: fenToState() now detects Shredder-FEN
      castling rights (any letter A-H/a-h in the castling field) and
      parses them via parseShredderCastling(). _parsePGN() extracts the
      [Variant "Chess960"] tag and returns it in the result; importPGN()
      calls setChess960Mode(true) + sets gameVariant='chess960' +
      derives SP-ID from the FEN back-rank.
  - assets/chess.src/game-logic.js: Added i18n strings for Chess960 UI
      (chess960_label, chess960_enable, chess960_spid, chess960_random,
      chess960_preview, chess960_note). Loading title updated to v1.0.4.
  - assets/chess.src/ui.js: New Game dialog gains Chess960 toggle,
      SP-ID input (0..959 or Random), and back-rank preview. _startGameImpl()
      now branches on dlgChess960: if true, calls initChess960State(spid)
      + setChess960Mode(true) + sets gameVariant/gameSPID; if false,
      calls initState() + setChess960Mode(false) and clears variant
      state. ECO openings are skipped in Chess960 mode (they assume
      the standard start position). Version badge → v1.0.4 (header,
      About dialog, render-error fallback page).
  - assets/chess.src/index.html.tpl: <title>Regalia v1.0.4</title>.
  - assets/stats.html: New "Heatmap Control Statistics" section that
      walks every position in the game, computes per-square attacker
      counts (cached by FEN), renders an 8x8 average-control heatmap
      (HSL background: blue=White-leaning, red=Black-leaning, purple=
      contested), and reports strongest/weakest squares for each side
      plus center-control trend (d4/e4/d5/e5 averages). New i18n
      strings added for all heatmap stats.
  - java/com/Regalia/StockfishNative.java: New @JavascriptInterface
      methods setChess960Mode(boolean) and isChess960Mode(). The
      _pendingChess960 flag is re-applied to the engine after every
      (auto-)restart via the new block in startEngine() after
      applySettings(). ENGINE_VERSION constant updated to "v1.0.4".
  - java/com/Regalia/MainActivity.java: VERSION constant updated to
      "v1.0.4".
  - java/com/Regalia/ChessApp.java: Log message updated to v1.0.4.
  - build.gradle: versionCode 104, versionName "1.0.4".
  - README.md, NOTICE, Regalia-v1.0.4-manual-zh.html,
      Regalia-v1.0.4-manual-en.html: all updated to v1.0.4.

v1.0.3 changes:
  - AndroidManifest.xml: versionCode/versionName bumped to 103 / "1.0.3".
  - res/values/strings.xml: app_name string updated to "Regalia v1.0.3".
  - assets/stats.html: NEW time-management analysis supporting TWO PGN time
    formats: (a) v1.0.3 direct {1.0s ...} format, (b) standard PGN
    [%clk HH:MM:SS] format with [TimeControl "BASE+INC"] header (used time
    derived via increment calculation). Also: clickable variation moves
    with synthetic-mainline reconstruction, FEN panel below the PGN text
    panel, variation text (...) rendered in italic. Bilingual UI strings
    added for all new features.
  - assets/chess.src/ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNComment() now uses a single
    space as separator between thinking time and eval annotation, e.g.
    "{3.2s +0.5 略优}". Backward-compatible with v1.0.2's space-separated
    format on the stats-page parsing side.
  - assets/chess.src/ui.js, game-logic.js: version strings updated to
    v1.0.3 (header badge, about dialog, loading title, built_in_only
    string).
  - assets/chess.src/index.html.tpl: <title> updated to "Regalia v1.0.3".

