  - No changes to AndroidManifest.xml, cpp/, res/, or stats.html.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev23 changes:
  - assets/chess.src/ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): eval cache debounce restored (150ms);
    onEngineRestarting/restartCurrentEngine no longer clear the entire cache;
    requestEngineEval dead second cache check removed; _buildPGNString dead
    `moveNum` variable removed.
  - assets/chess.src/ui.js (GPL v3): _pgnCacheOnSearchInput stale 🔍 comment fixed.
  - assets/chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.
  - java/com/Regalia/StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): saveEvalCacheSync() now uses
    Files.move() with ATOMIC_MOVE + REPLACE_EXISTING on API 26+ for true
    POSIX-atomic rename (eliminates the delete+rename data-loss window).
  - No changes to AndroidManifest.xml, cpp/, res/, or stats.html.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev24 changes:
  - assets/chess.src/ai-bridge.js (GPL v3): analyze-all root-cause fix (5
    distinct bugs: all-cached short-circuit, per-step safety timer with
    skip-stuck-step, onEngineReady batch resume, cache-hit advance during
    batch, onEngineError no longer drops batch). New globals _humanPlayerName,
    playerWhite, playerBlack. _buildPGNString(forceIncludeVariations) —
    new parameter for PGN cache archive completeness. requestEngineEval()
    cache-hit-during-batch advance. onEngineReady() batch resume.
  - assets/chess.src/game-logic.js (GPL v3): NEW i18n keys for rename feature
    (rename_player_hint, rename_player_prompt, rename_player_saved,
    rename_player_reset — zh/en).
  - assets/chess.src/tablebase.js (GPL v3): _parsePGN() extracts [%eval ...]
    tags from {} comments BEFORE stripping them (returns extractedEvals array).
    importPGN() populates _reviewEvalCache from extracted evals (selectively
    clearing only current game's entries, preserving other games' caches).
    Also extracts playerWhite/playerBlack from PGN headers and populates
    _humanPlayerName if the human player's slot has a non-default name.
  - assets/chess.src/ui.js (GPL v3): reviewAnalyzeAll() rewritten (all-cached
    short-circuit + per-step safety timer). _reviewAnalyzeResetSafetyTimer()
    new helper. Player bar uses _humanPlayerName; clicking opens
    _renameHumanPlayer() prompt. _pgnCacheSaveCurrent() ALWAYS uses
    _buildPGNString(true). Removed redundant 📥 Import button from PGN Cache
    Manager. _startGameImpl() clears playerWhite/playerBlack.
  - assets/chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.
  - jniLibs/arm64-v8a/libstockfish.so (GPL v3): updated to the official
    Stockfish 18 sf_18 release, arm64-v8a-dotprod variant (NDK r27c build,
    114 MB, NEON+dotprod acceleration for optimal performance on modern
    ARM64 devices).
  - No changes to AndroidManifest.xml, cpp/, res/, java/, or stats.html.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev25 changes:
  - assets/chess.src/ui.js (GPL v3): New Game dialog — removed redundant
    <h3>${T('chess960_label')} heading above Chess960 dedicated settings.
    The Chess960 toggle label already makes the mode clear; settings now
    appear directly under the toggle.
  - assets/chess.html: rebuilt from the above chess.src/ changes.
  - assets/stats.html (GPL v3): renderPGNText() → renderSAN() — promotion
    symbols now rendered as side-colored piece symbols (♕/♛, ♖/♜, ♗/♝,
    ♘/♞) instead of literal letters. Shared _replacePromo() helper handles
    both pawn-move and piece-move branches uniformly.
  - No changes to AndroidManifest.xml, cpp/, res/, java/, or jniLibs/.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev26 changes:
  - assets/stats.html (GPL v3): renderPGNText() — ROOT-CAUSE FIX for
    "e8=Q still shows letter" bug. The SAN regex's pawn non-capture
    alternative was [a-h][1-8][+#]? (NO promotion group), so "e8=Q"
    matched only "e8" — leaving "=Q" as raw literal text. Rev26 fixes the
    alternative to [a-h][1-8](?:=[QRBN])?[+#]?, which captures the full
    "e8=Q" so renderSAN()/_replacePromo() can convert the promotion piece
    to a symbol. Same fix applied to the variation-move regex.
  - No changes to AndroidManifest.xml, cpp/, res/, java/, jniLibs/, or
    chess.html.

